{{About|the painter|the chemistry professor|Helen M. Berman}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox artist | bgcolour = | name = Helen Berman | image = Helen - Grey Sun.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Grey Sun, 1997 | birth_name = Hélène Julia Cohen | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1936|4|6}} | birth_place = [[Amsterdam]], Netherlands | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = | field = [[Painting]], [[Drawing]], [[Industrial design|Design]] | training = [[Kees Bol]], [[Jan Gregoor]], [[Thierry Veltman]] | alma_mater = [[Design Academy Eindhoven]] | konown_for = [[painting]], [[drawing]], [[textile design]] | style = [[Modern art]], [[Postmodern art]] | movement = [[Abstract expressionism]], [[Lyrical abstraction]] | works = | patrons = | influenced by = [[Paul Klee|Klee]],<ref name="Argov"/> [[Paul Cézanne|Cézanne]],<ref name="GeldInfl">{{cite book |last= Geldman |first= Mordechai |authorlink= Mordechai Geldman |title= Helen Berman: Sharon Landscapes |year= 2009 |place= Israel}}</ref> [[Nicolas de Staël|De&nbsp;Staël]],<ref name="GeldInfl"/> [[Georges-Pierre Seurat|Seurat]], [[J. M. W. Turner|Turner]]<ref name="GeldInfl"/> | influenced = | awards = Van Dissel [[textile design]] awards }}
'''Helen Berman''' ({{lang-he|הלן ברמן}}; born 6 April 1936) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]]-[[Israel]]i [[visual arts|visual artist]]. She was a [[textile designer]] in the 1960s and has been a [[Painting|painter]] and occasionally an [[Art education|art educator]] since the 1970s. She is well known in Israel and has exhibited also in Germany and the Netherlands. She created [[modern art|modern]] and [[postmodern art]] and has engaged in realistic [[impressionism]] and lyrical [[abstract expressionism]].<ref name="Geldman"/>
==Biography== Helen Berman was born in [[Amsterdam]] and as a young girl survived the [[Holocaust]].<ref>{{cite book | first = Thijs | last = Berman | authorlink = Thijs Berman | title = Op zoek naar [[George Fles]] | publisher = [[Van Gennep]] | location = [[Amsterdam]] | page = 27 | quote = Hélène, een aangetrouwde tante die zelf de oorlog tenauwernood overleefde... | language = Dutch | year = 1993 | isbn = 90-6012-992-X }}</ref><ref name="Baiki">{{cite journal | last = Berman | first = Helen | title = An Enchanted Dream Came True | work = [[Báiki]] | issue = 24 | year = 2002 | page = 22 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.salom.com.tr/news/detail/2316-Yahudi-kurtaranlara-odul.aspx | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110719072138/http://www.salom.com.tr/news/detail/2316-Yahudi-kurtaranlara-odul.aspx | archivedate = 2011-07-19 | title = Yahudi kurtaranlara ödül | language = Turkish | work = Şalom | date = 18 June 2006 | accessdate = 26 September 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bevrijdingsportretten.nl/portret/ernst-elisabeth-helene-cohen/|title=Ernst, Elisabeth & Helene Cohen|work=Bevrijdingsportretten|publisher=Herinneringscentrum Kamp Westerbork}}</ref> She was trained as a [[textile]] [[designer]] at the [[Design Academy Eindhoven]].<ref name="IMJ">{{citation|work=Israeli Art Center|url=http://www.imj.org.il/artcenter/default.asp?artist=272140|archive-url=https://archive.is/20121218195444/http://www.imj.org.il/artcenter/default.asp?artist=272140|dead-url=yes|archive-date=18 December 2012|title=Helen Berman|publisher=[[Israel Museum]]|location=[[Jerusalem]]|accessdate=28 June 2008|language=Hebrew}}</ref> While at the academy, she took extracurricular coursework in the [[free arts]] with [[Kees Bol]] and [[Jan Gregoor]].<ref name="Geldman">{{cite book |last= Geldman |first= Mordechai |authorlink= Mordechai Geldman |title= Helen Berman: Sharon Landscapes |year= 2009 |location= Israel}}</ref> After her graduation in 1960, Helen Berman designed textiles for several companies. Some of her designs were awarded prizes and publications in professional magazines.
During the seventies, Berman studied [[painting]] and [[drawing]] with [[Thierry Veltman]],<ref name="Sneh">{{cite news|last=Sneh|first=Nachum|title=View to the Past and Future in the Exhibition of a Painter Who Immigrated from the Netherlands|publisher=[[Yediot Ahronot]]|newspaper=Kol Hanegev|date=27 May 1983|language=Hebrew}}</ref> graduating with a teaching degree. In 1978, she immigrated to [[Israel]], where she continued to refine her style. During a decade-long residence in [[Jaffa, Israel|Jaffa]], she became part of the local artists' community and a member of the Israel Painters and Sculptors Association. Since 1998, she has been painting and exhibiting from her studio in [[Tel Mond]].
