'''Jason Lindsey''' aka "Mr. Science" is an award-winning [[natural science|science]] [[teacher|educator]], [[author]], [[meteorologist]], and one of only seven [[STEM fields|STEM]] Certified Master Trainers in [[United States|America]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lindsey |first1=Jason |url=http://www.surfky.com/index.php/component/content/article/123-general-news-for-all-sites/54727-local-educator-one-of-only-seven-stem-certified-master-trainers |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150101223719/http://www.surfky.com/index.php/component/content/article/123-general-news-for-all-sites/54727-local-educator-one-of-only-seven-stem-certified-master-trainers |dead-url=yes |archive-date=January 1, 2015 |accessdate=1 January 2015 |publisher=Surfky |date=November 13, 2014 }}</ref> Lindsey [[television producer|produces]] and [[television presenter|hosts]] a popular [[television]] segment called Hooked on Science.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lindseyf|first1=Jason|url=http://hookedonscience.org/televisionsegment.html|website=www.hookedonscience.org|publisher=Hooked on Science|accessdate=1 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Lindsey|first1=Jason|url=http://www.wpsdlocal6.com/category/281328/hooked-on-science|website=www.wpsdlocal6.com|publisher=Paxton Media, LLC|accessdate=1 January 2015}}</ref> Each year, he performs hands-on [[science experiments]] at hundreds of [[school]]s and community events throughout the United States. His goal is to make kids inquisitive about the world around them and to get them to develop a long-term interest in science and [[math]]. Jason can also be seen forecasting the weather on several local television stations across the US as a freelance broadcast meteorologist. In recent years he has only been seen on WPSD, a television station in Paducah, KY and [[WEHT]], a television station in [[Evansville, IN]]. Jason can also frequently be seen performing science experiments on NBC's Today Show. <ref>{{cite news|last1=Lindsey|first1=Jason|url=http://www.kentuckymonthly.com/living/education/the-science-guy/|accessdate=1 January 2015|agency=Magazine|publisher=Kentucky Monthly|date=July 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.today.com/video/-mr-science-jason-lindsey-shows-how-to-make-explosive-bubbles-1210167875754|title=‘Mr. Science’ Jason Lindsey shows how to make explosive bubbles|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tristatehomepage.com/contact/bios/jason-lindsey/176287552|title=Jason Lindsey|date=28 February 2018|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wpsdlocal6.com/bios/jason-lindsey/|title=Jason Lindsey - WPSD Local 6|publisher=}}</ref>

