{{orphan|date=September 2014}} '''STARTALK''' is a language education program at the [[University of Maryland, College Park|University of Maryland]], created under the [[National Security Language Initiative]], a federal program which seeks to expand the teaching of strategically important languages in the United States. Languages taught under the STARTALK program include [[Arabic language|Arabic]], [[Chinese language|Chinese]], [[Dari language|Dari]], [[Hindi]], [[Persian language|Persian]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], [[Russian language|Russian]], [[Swahili language|Swahili]], [[Turkish language|Turkish]], and [[Urdu]]. STARTALK is a project of the [[National Foreign Language Center]] of the University of Maryland, located in [[Riverdale, Anne Arundel County, Maryland|Riverdale, Maryland]].<ref name="umd">{{cite web | title = Welcome to STARTALK! | work = STARTALK | publisher = University of Maryland | url = https://startalk.umd.edu/}}</ref>
